    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">What is PCG-MAS?</div>
      <p>PCG-MAS — <strong>Proof-Carrying Generation for Multi-Agent Systems</strong> — is a framework where every generated answer is verified by four independent channels before being shown to the user. If any channel rejects, the answer is withheld and the user sees the rejection reason instead of a fabricated one.</p>

      <div class="card-title spaced">Comparison with baselines</div>
      <table class="table">
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Evidence committed</th><th>Replayable</th><th>Entailment checked</th><th>Risk controlled</th><th>Audit trail</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Raw LLM</td><td>no</td><td>no</td><td>no</td><td>no</td><td>no</td></tr>
          <tr><td>RAG</td><td>partial</td><td>no</td><td>no</td><td>no</td><td>partial</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Self-consistency sampling</td><td>no</td><td>partial</td><td>no</td><td>no</td><td>no</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Verifier-only post-hoc</td><td>partial</td><td>no</td><td>yes</td><td>no</td><td>partial</td></tr>
          <tr><td><strong>PCG-MAS</strong></td><td><strong>yes</strong></td><td><strong>yes</strong></td><td><strong>yes</strong></td><td><strong>yes</strong></td><td><strong>yes</strong></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <div class="card-title spaced">BYOK — bring your own key</div>
      <p>This space runs on free CPU. To call a frontier model, you provide your own API key (OpenAI, Anthropic, DeepSeek, Hugging Face). Your key is never logged, never persisted, never leaves your browser session.</p>
